appears to be controlled by the deviation vector from the layer-mean wind. Although the schemes using vertical shear are shown to perform somewhat better on average than schemes based on the mean wind alone, there are times in which they also result in large forecast errors. The results demonstrate the inherent difficulty in using an observed hodograph to predict supercell motion.{\textless}/p{\textgreater}{\textless}/section{\textgreater}},
